comments.text:
I was at a zoo one time with my son and daughter.  Daughter was still too little to talk and the son was still pretty little.  

My son saw two camels going at it and asked me what they were doing, I said, "Celebrating Wednesday."  He looked at me confused, (he knew his days of the week and knew it was Saturday) and asked, "Wednesday?"  I nodded and said, "Yup, hump day."  He laughed and said, "Oh becuase camels have humps and Wednesday is Hump Day."  He had heard his mom call Wednesday hump day more than a few times so the joke landed and he had no more questions.

Lil' guy repeated an iteration of the joke, "What's a camels favorite day?  Wednesday because its hump day!" for a while.  Funny as it was, thank goodness he never tried to celebrate Wednesday like a camel when he was little.
